<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="enterprise-metrics">Enterprise metrics</h2>

<p>Enterprise metrics track portfolio-wide performance indicators that span multiple products and services. These metrics provide a high-level view of digital delivery performance across the department.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Submitting enterprise metrics</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Enterprise metrics</strong></li>
    <li>View the enterprise metrics dashboard showing all configured metrics</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Submit metrics"</strong> for the reporting period</li>
    <li>Enter values for each metric:
        <ul>
            <li>Text metrics: Enter descriptive text</li>
            <li>Number metrics: Enter whole numbers</li>
            <li>Decimal metrics: Enter decimal values</li>
            <li>Percentage metrics: Enter values from 0-100%</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Add commentary or notes where relevant</li>
    <li>Link metrics to strategic objectives if applicable</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Submit"</strong> to save</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing metric history</h3>

<p>View historical enterprise metric submissions to track trends over time:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Navigate to the enterprise metrics dashboard</li>
    <li>Click on a metric to view its history</li>
    <li>View line charts showing trends</li>
    <li>Compare values across reporting periods</li>
    <li>Export historical data for analysis</li>
</ul>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Enterprise metrics are typically submitted monthly or quarterly by central operations teams. Contact your administrator if you need access to submit enterprise metrics.</p>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="functional-standards">Functional standards</h2>

<p>Functional standards assessments enable product teams to demonstrate compliance with DDaT (Digital, Data and Technology) functional standards. Assessments are conducted at the product level against specific standards and criteria.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Conducting an assessment</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Functional standards</strong></li>
    <li>Select the product to assess</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Conduct assessment"</strong></li>
    <li>Select the functional standard to assess against</li>
    <li>Navigate through standards by theme and practice area</li>
    <li>For each criterion:
        <ul>
            <li>Read the criterion description</li>
            <li>Select a compliance level (Not met, Partially met, Fully met)</li>
            <li>Provide evidence of compliance (upload files or add links)</li>
            <li>Add notes or explanations</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Save as draft to continue later, or submit when complete</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Assessment workflow</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Draft:</strong> Assessment in progress, can be edited</li>
    <li><strong>Submitted:</strong> Assessment complete and submitted</li>
    <li><strong>Under review:</strong> Assessment being reviewed by assessors</li>
    <li><strong>Approved:</strong> Assessment approved and compliance confirmed</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing assessment history</h3>

<p>Track compliance progress over time by viewing historical assessments:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Navigate to functional standards for a product</li>
    <li>View list of completed assessments</li>
    <li>Click on an assessment to view details</li>
    <li>Compare assessments over time to track improvements</li>
    <li>View compliance trends and gaps</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="strategic-objectives">Strategic objectives</h2>

<p>Strategic objectives represent high-level organisational goals. Products, projects, milestones, risks, and actions can be linked to strategic objectives to demonstrate strategic alignment.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing strategic objectives</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Strategic objectives</strong></li>
    <li>Browse the list of current strategic objectives</li>
    <li>Click on an objective to view details:
        <ul>
            <li>Objective description and status</li>
            <li>Linked products</li>
            <li>Linked projects</li>
            <li>Associated risks and issues</li>
            <li>Supporting actions and milestones</li>
            <li>Overall progress tracking</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Linking items to objectives</h3>

<p>Link products, projects, RAID items, and milestones to strategic objectives:</p>

<ol>
    <li>When creating or editing an item (product, project, risk, issue, action, milestone)</li>
    <li>Find the <strong>Strategic objectives</strong> field (usually a multi-select dropdown)</li>
    <li>Select one or more relevant objectives</li>
    <li>Save the item</li>
    <li>The item will now appear in the strategic objective's linked items list</li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> Linking items to strategic objectives helps demonstrate how delivery work contributes to organisational goals. This is valuable for portfolio reviews and strategic reporting.</p>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="compliance">Compliance tracking</h2>

<p>The compliance dashboard provides a portfolio-wide view of functional standards compliance across all products and standards.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Compliance dashboard</h3>

<p>The compliance dashboard shows:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Compliance by product:</strong> View compliance status for each product</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance by standard:</strong> See which products meet each standard</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance by theme:</strong> Group compliance by standard themes</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance by practice area:</strong> View compliance by practice area</li>
    <li><strong>Visual indicators:</strong> RAG status (Red, Amber, Green) for compliance levels</li>
    <li><strong>Gap analysis:</strong> Identify areas of non-compliance requiring attention</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using the compliance dashboard</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Compliance dashboard</strong></li>
    <li>Use filters to focus on specific:
        <ul>
            <li>Products</li>
            <li>Standards</li>
            <li>Themes</li>
            <li>Practice areas</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>View compliance heat map for visual overview</li>
    <li>Export compliance reports for stakeholders</li>
    <li>Track compliance trends over time</li>
</ol>

